This game uses assets from the 1983 Smith & Wesson Identi-Kit Model II.

The Identi-Kit was a facial compositing tool used by law enforcement to compile facial features into a cohesive sketch from witness descriptions.

These composites were responsible for criminal convictions, and this game makes no attempt to diminish the seriousness of its contents.
